question: What was the predominant rotavirus genotype in the pre-vaccine era, in Australia?
ideal_answer: G1P[8] was the dominant genotype in Australia in the prevaccine era (1995-2006).

snippets.text: G1P[8] was the dominant genotype nationally in the prevaccine era (1995-2006).

From 1995 to 2015, the Australian Rotavirus Surveillance Program conducted genotypic analysis on 13051 rotavirus-positive samples from children <5 years of age, hospitalized with acute gastroenteritis.
In the pre-vaccine era, G1P[8] was most prevalent, ranging from 39% (411/1,057) to 74% (527/709) per year.
